# Comms public navigation

## Header Learn menu (keep this shape)

Three groups in [`Header.tsx`](src/components/layout/Header.tsx) `learnGroups`:

1. **Guides** — Comms Resources, The Blueprint, Strike Guide, Photo Consent (`/guide/photo-consent`)
2. **By channel** — Print Guide (`/guide/print`), Union Boards Guide, Website Guide
3. **Libraries** — Social Examples, Captions

Do not re-flatten channel guides into a long top-level link bar. Do not promote `/manifesto` into Header (quiet home trust link by design). Do not promote `/install` into Header (muted footer + support/privacy cross-links only — see `.cursor/rules/pwa.mdc`).

## Header Tools menu (keep this shape)

Four groups in `Header.tsx` `toolGroups` (same sectioned dropdown pattern as Learn):

1. **Brand** — Logo Builder, Resizer, Document & Slide Generator
2. **Union boards** — Board Banner & Trim, Board Notice Maker, Solidarity Posters, QR Board Posters, QR Link Cards
3. **Print** — Flyer Maker
4. **Social & web** — Graphic Maker, Quote Card, Meeting Backgrounds, Website Template, Alt-Text Assistant

Do not re-flatten Tools into a single ungrouped list. Keep one **Tools ▾** trigger — do not add extra top-level tool links.

## Footer

Include Print Guide alongside Blueprint / Examples / Captions / Resources so print-first locals are not chrome-orphaned. Privacy, Accessibility, Support stay in footer. **Install as an app** (`/install`) is a muted text link under the footer blurb — not a peer of Privacy/Support in the footer nav row.

## Brand Assets

`/assets` is not a Header top-level item. Link from Brand Kit (`brandKit.assetsLink`). Home Brand Kit card may mention assets in copy; prefer a real route link on Brand Kit.

## Keep out of public chrome

- Operator docs (`docs/guides/SETUP.md`, `DEPLOY.md`)
- Hub modules (use `HubNav`)
- Invented marketing routes (`/about`, `/pricing`, `/blog`) unless product expands
- PWA install guide (`/install`) — quiet only; never Learn/Tools/Header

